    "exact_authorization_text": "I approve the bounded CAL-001-P3D-W01 false-positive review, implementation correction, and reauthorization decision:\n\nPASS_REVIEW_CORRECT_AND_REAUTHORIZE_W01_AFTER_LOCAL_CREDIT_CONTINUITY_FALSE_POSITIVE.\n\nThis decision is bound to repository commit 7c86367a3d7ca17bb63e8ad148144b3075f4dab7 and preserves the prior CAL-001-P3C authorization text SHA-256:\n\n73ae380b9af11656660d47755da1690b8ab234afcaf99795cf1743365bdd1392\n\nIt also preserves the accepted remaining-task ordered-list SHA-256:\n\n783cb601ce9f33f20defadce9b37aff33698dcf492b9b71273a023e4deb0e291\n\nI accept the following established facts:\n\n- no W01 submit occurred;\n- no submit_id or logid was created;\n- no query or download occurred;\n- no provider media was created;\n- no credits were consumed by W01;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 never entered the durable duplicate-prevention submit transition;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 submit_attempt_count remains zero;\n- the observed immediate pre-submit balance was 6045;\n- the authorized F01 balance threshold was 5950;\n- 6045 satisfied the authorized threshold;\n- the additional requirement that 6045 equal the earlier observation of 5957 was not part of the human authorization;\n- the resulting stop was a local pre-submit validation false positive, not a provider failure, submit failure, command-contract failure, or budget-threshold failure.\n\nBefore W01 authority may reopen, a strictly no-live correction phase must:\n\n1. Recompute the five accepted immutable digests using the exact canonical definitions already accepted by CAL-001-P3C.\n\n2. Require the following exact accepted values:\n\n- fixed_manifest_sha256=b2ecfb87899feca784fc8e1f2b751fc181aeab9a9118a3a7609067d4b92b2c6d\n- fixture_registry_sha256=cf35a7ea15e4c51e4d6936f9a796f90215445f059503cd29bd6eccb8c7658142\n- prompt_inventory_sha256=27c95725e80c325693894f8b04cc3587f404f971559fbf1c2cc9292b3a361d6d\n- package_inventory_sha256=b716cb063977172a8fcf28359c4ceef00b9ad0f90524a3ee675d194fb79c251c\n- full_experiment_inventory_sha256=448a2d473b06bf4b5f8548644733fdd68af7cb37749bc8d807bf69e53ef96138\n\n3. Investigate the different package-inventory and full-inventory values written in the historical W01 stop report.\n\nIf the accepted bytes or canonical accepted digests actually differ, stop without reopening authority.\n\nIf the difference is only a report-field, temporary-driver, or canonicalization defect:\n\n- preserve the historical W01 stop report unchanged;\n- record the discrepancy and corrected interpretation in a new decision report;\n- do not rewrite historical evidence;\n- use the accepted P3C canonical digests for future gates.\n\n4. Correct only the local credit-continuity validation implementation that imposed exact equality with the earlier balance observation.\n\nThe corrected rule must be:\n\n- the current balance must be numeric;\n- the current balance must satisfy the authorized dynamic threshold;\n- a positive balance change before submit is recorded as positive_nonspend_credit_drift and does not enlarge task scope or budget;\n- a negative balance change before submit, when no authorized CAL-001 submit occurred between observations, is an unexplained_negative_credit_drift stop condition;\n- after an authorized submit, the immediate pre-submit minus post-submit balance must equal exactly 70;\n- provider credit_count must also equal exactly 70.\n\n5. Add and pass bounded no-live tests covering:\n\n- prior observation 5957, current observation 6045, required threshold 5950: pass;\n- current observation below the required threshold: stop;\n- unexplained negative pre-submit drift with no intervening authorized submit: stop;\n- exact post-submit 70-credit reconciliation: pass;\n- any absent, nonnumeric, ambiguous, or non-70 submit charge: stop.\n\n6. Correct future evidence field naming so that:\n\n- authorization_text_sha256 means 73ae380b9af11656660d47755da1690b8ab234afcaf99795cf1743365bdd1392;\n- authorization_record_file_sha256 means 983ea0c8f95ef018b3171e41bc97a93235f8199796225335190f0156047e7141.\n\n7. Preserve all W01 stop evidence, subprocess envelopes, parsed credit records, and the commit at which authority was closed.\n\n8. After all correction gates pass, update the resumable state so that:\n\n- macro_state=ACTIVATED_READY;\n- W01 wave_state=pending;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 task_state=pending_preflight;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 submit_attempt_count=0;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 submit_id=null;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 query_count=0;\n- CAL001-F01-P1-R1 download_count=0;\n- next_wave_id=W01;\n- next_experiment_id=CAL001-F01-P1-R1;\n- execution_authority_active=true;\n- remaining_noncanary_tasks_authorized=true.\n\n9. Reauthorization remains limited to the existing W01 seven-task P1-R1 wave in strict F01 through F07 order.\n\n10. Commit and push the correction, tests, reauthorization record, updated resumable state, and new decision report. Authority is not effective unless push succeeds and local HEAD equals origin/main.\n\nThis correction phase must perform no Dreamina command, including version, user_credit, help, login, submit, query_result, download, list_task, or session.\n\nIt must consume zero credits and create no media.\n\nThis decision does not authorize:\n\n- W02 or any later wave;\n- retry or resubmit;\n- duplicate submit;\n- Prompt, package, fixture, manifest, or accepted inventory changes;\n- task replacement or expansion;\n- Source modification;\n- CAL-001B;\n- automatic visual scoring;\n- family-winner or global Prompt-winner selection;\n- media finalization;\n- final_master=true;\n- locked=true.\n\nAfter the no-live correction phase succeeds, W01 may resume from CAL001-F01-P1-R1 under a separately executed bounded live-wave Goal. The historical false-positive stop must not be counted as a submit attempt, retry, or resubmit.",
